	<div class="comment_text">
	<p>GREAT history! Jim was always true to his values. He was willing to bring the problem to the students regardless of what people might think. His commitment  to fight racism was not just idle words! </p>
<p>That same year a bunch of us got together at Parkland and ran for student government on the platform of black representation. Up until then most all the student government was made up of white politically connected kids. The campaign pitted &#8220;regular&#8221; people against the &#8220;elite&#8221; crowd. We were successful with Don elected as President, I was elected Vice President, that year Parkland  elected Terry Townsend as the first black student government representative.</p>
	</div>

	<div class="comment_author vcard">
